Maintanance web services specification
======================================

Source: Provozní řád ISDS, version 2008-30-06, Pages 13–14
Source: Webové služby ISDS pro podporu procesů, version 2009-06-26


These services are intended for administration of box as such. NONE of the
services MARK incoming messages as delivered.

SOAP web services defined in: db_manipulations.wsdl, db_supplementary.wsdl
(Appendix 3 of Provozní řád ISDS)

Data types: dbTypes.xsd (Appendix 3)

Documentation: DataBox_ws.pdf, System_ws.doc (Appendix 3)

Note: OVM mode is defined in paragraph 5a of Czech ISDS Act (300/2008 Coll.)

List of SOAP requests follows.


db_manipulations.wsdl
=====================

URL postfix: DsManage

CreateDataBox
    Create box
DeleteDataBox
    Remove box
UpdateDataBoxDescr
    Change data about box owner
AddDataBoxUser
    Add person permitted access to the box
DeleteDataBoxUser
    Remove person permitted to access to the box
UpdateDataBoxUser
    Change data about permitted person
NewAccessData
    Reset access data (remove old ones and generates new ones)
DisableDataBoxExternally
    Make box unaccessible because owner lost ability to use the box for legal
    reasons (prisoned person, person with no or weak legal rights)
DisableOwnDataBox
    Make box unaccessable on request of its owner
EnableOwnDataBox
    Renew access to the box
SetEffectiveOVM
    Switch box into OVM mode
CleareEffectiveOVM
    Set box of OVM mode


db_supplementary.wsdl
=====================

URL postfix: DsManage

GetDataBoxUsers
    Get list of users permitted to access the box.
GetOwnerInfoFromLogin
    Get data about logged in user and his (current) box.
StoreAccessDataDeliveryInfo
    Save date when credentials has been (out-of-band) delivered to user.
